<br>
Actually, I think 95% of the server population [EDIT: and SoE] would be quite happy if the 5% at the top vanished from the face of Norrath. never to be seen again.<br>
<br>
EDIT: In fact, the more I think about it...  How many uberguilds have good things to say about SoE and EQ?  I'll amend my statement above....<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
----------------------<br>
<br>
As for the Warrior vs. Knight crusade, Furor's a tool.  That fool's been waving his dick in the air so long, I don't think even he remembers why... I think he just likes waving it.<br>
<br>
His latest claims of Knights out-tanking Warriors is utter bullshit.  It's not like some Knight new to Time tanked their guild through to Quarm.  Knights, after getting decked in PoTime gear are able to go back and tank the mobs their guilds have been farming for months... big whoop.  That has been the case forever.  If a Knight couldn't be one rounded by a mob, then we could tank it.<br>
<br>
Warriors have always been the best raid tank.  Disc defensive is a huge factor in that in ultra-high DPS fights and things like AE Taunt allow for reliable switches between tanks.  Knights may be kings of maintaining aggro, but we have absolutely no guaranteed way of gaining aggro at will.  Unless they've been deliberately trying to take aggro the whole fight, the mobs will usually rape half the rotation and wizards before a Knight gets them under control.  Defensive AA like Tactical Mastery and Stalwart Endurance help a great deal as well.<br>
<br>
Knights have always been good tanks.  Hell, I was Isengard's MT until that slacker Devon finally leveled and got disc defensive.  Knights tanking while the guild is farming months old content is not a big deal, it has always been and probably will always be [and should be] Warriors who first mastered that content.<br>
<br>
Furor's ravings about the injustice of HAVING to have a Knight at a certain raid, lest he be forced to call it off, just prove how far out in left field that guy is.  Excuse me???  How many raids in the history of EQ have been called off for lack of Warriors, Clerics, Enchanters, Shaman, etc.  I would certainly hope, that somewhere in EQ there's a raid where you actually NEED a Knight. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5948">Duke Krazaak Crushbone</a> &lt<a href="http://www.hneguild.com">Heaven and Earth</a>&gt<BR>
